item.title: Go, fuck yourself, scumbag.
item.description: https://apnews.com/article/trump-kennedy-center-performing-arts-8b7159067174f3a0070b877c149ff0a7 This really pisses me off. I'm from Philadelphia but spent decades in the DC region. I raised my kids taking advantage of all the things DC had to offer. When you live in the region, you don't have to cram everything into one or two days. You can spend an entire day at the Zoo, an entire day at the American History museum, an entire day at (my personal favorite) the Natural History museum. Just walking the mall can take up a whole day. At least once a year we did a show at the Kennedy Center, usually the touring Musicals but a number of other events. I used to be proud of our nations capital. Now I avoid it like the plague Also, fuck this guy. I guess he is the definition of "and the band played on" https://washingtonian.com/2025/12/17/a-kennedy-center-musician-on-what-its-like-there-now/

item.title: At just 18 years old, she ran toward gunfire so others could live.
item.description: At just 18 years old, she ran toward gunfire so others could live. Sgt. Monica Lin Brown, an Army medic with the 82nd Airborne, charged through exploding mortars and enemy fire in Afghanistan to save her wounded brothers after an IED ambush—shielding them with her own body. The first woman in the Afghanistan War and only the second since WWII to receive the Silver Star. A true American hero. ?? God bless Sgt. Monica Lin Brown. Source: Wikipedia, Monica Lin Brown.
